wikipedia-extract: Silicon is a chemical element with the symbol Si and atomic number 14. It is a hard, brittle crystalline solid with a blue-grey metallic luster, and is a tetravalent metalloid and semiconductor. It is a member of group 14 in the periodic table: [[carbon|Carbon]] is above it; and [[germanium|Germanium]], [[tin|Tin]], [[lead|Lead]], and [[flerovium|Flerovium]] are below it. It is relatively unreactive.
